<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-32] thrift.el doesn&apos;t syntax highlight single line comments correctly in xemacs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-32</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;single line (// style) comments end up syntax highlighting like /* in my version of xemacs. The following patch fixes the issue for me:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;diff --git a/thrift.el b/thrift.el
index 736b720..3b9026b 100644
--- a/thrift.el
+++ b/thrift.el
@@ -87,7 +87,7 @@
 (defvar thrift-mode-syntax-table
   (let ((thrift-mode-syntax-table (make-syntax-table)))
     (modify-syntax-entry ?_ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;w&quot;&lt;/span&gt; thrift-mode-syntax-table)
-    (modify-syntax-entry ?/ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;. 124b&quot;&lt;/span&gt; thrift-mode-syntax-table)
+    (modify-syntax-entry ?/ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;. 1456&quot;&lt;/span&gt; thrift-mode-syntax-table)
     (modify-syntax-entry ?* &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;. 23&quot;&lt;/span&gt; thrift-mode-syntax-table)
     (modify-syntax-entry ?\n &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&amp;gt; b&quot;&lt;/span&gt; thrift-mode-syntax-table)
     thrift-mode-syntax-table)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
